node.text: Happy Father’s Day, @cole.labrant 💞 We all love you so much. You go above and beyond for your family & we have no idea what we would do without you. You love your kids like crazy & you’ve got this whole dad thing down to a T by now. You blew all of my expectations out of the water... I’m always so amazed by you. I love you beyond! I hope you feel special today❤️

node.text: I love this sweet girl. She radiates JOY! She is such a gift to our family. I sure do love watching her play soccer and try new things. I think activities are so good to keep kids busy and teach them important things in life. My kids could be the best or the worst at whatever they do, and I would have the same reaction. What I hope the most for my kids is that they love Jesus, love people, and bring kindness and light into everything they do. & this girl does such a great job at that already. Im so proud of your sweet heart, Posie Rayne! ❤️⚽️

node.text: Well... my cute valentine boy. You’ve been my valentine since you were 19 & you went from zero valentines to TWO right off the bat. You already know how much I adore you & think the world of you.. but I want you to know how our kids think the same exact thing. They see it all. The time you put in to play with them & talk with them. The effort you put in to make sure they realize how much you love their mom. The passion you have for Jesus. They see it ALL! Posie says “awww cute” every time you kiss me.. even tho everleigh now says “ewww”🤷🏼‍♀️ Life is so fun with you. Parenting is even more fun with you. You make us your priority. You make God an even bigger priority. & it shows. Everyone who knows you knows how insanely amazing you are. Lucky I get to be your valentine forever. Swipe to see our 3 other cute valentines ❤️

node.text:
Well.. we’ve got a 6 month old in the house! He’s so loved & his big sisters are his #1 fans. I love these 3 so much😭 All I really want is for my kids to grow up knowing Jesus, to have nothing but kindness in their hearts for others, & to know I did my very best to love and raise them right. I’m so proud of them already & so beyond blessed to be their mama💖 
Proverbs 31:25-30
📸: @patty.othon
